T~L~1815~-445~0~#0000FF~sans-serif~10pt~normal~undefined~~comment~These are in groups of three leds in series with a current limiting resistor
that works for 12V. You can copy and paste these along with the dimmer circuit
above into your pcb design, to have as many backlight leds as you need. The 
resistor here is a surface mount one, that can be soldered with an iron too, 
but feel free to replace it with a through-hole version if you want.~1~start~gge273~0~pinpart

T~L~595~130~0~#0000FF~~5.5pt~~~~comment~The backlight pin on pin D13 will blink when the module
boots and during serial port traffic, because it has 
the built in led also on the Mega 2560. 
 
This will not happen after Mobiflight runs. But just 
something to be aware of. If that bothers you, swap it
with some other PWM capable pin (D2-D12)~1~start~gge21005~0~pinpart
